<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08081</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REQUIRING THE ESTABLISHMENT OF FULLY-EQUIPPED SCIENCE LABORATORIES IN EVERY PUBLIC ELEMENTARY AND SECONDARY SCHOOL AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Provides infrastructure projects for the upgrade, maintenance and development of laboratory rooms and facilities in all elementary and secondary schools. 
Gives tax incentives to private entities engaging in S&T development; 20% tax deduction from the total revenue obligations for private schools who shall import laboratory equipment/facilities for the exclusive use in their school; 3% tax incentive from the importation of raw materials for private entities engaged in the manufacture of laboratory equipment needed in public schools.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Science Laboratory for Basic Education Act.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SY-ALVARADO, JOSE ANTONIO &quot;KUYA JONATHAN&quot; R.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-09</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2018-09-20)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON BASIC EDUCATION AND CULTURE ON 2018-08-14</td></tr></table>